%% Pudel Slash Command Flow v2.2.1
%% Two-Tier Sync + Components V2 Settings Panel

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Discord User
    participant Discord as Discord API
    participant JDA as JDA 6
    participant Listener as InteractionEventListener
    participant Manager as InteractionManagerImpl
    participant Handler as @SlashCommand Handler
    participant CV2 as Components V2 Panel
    participant Brain as PudelBrain (optional)

    Note over User,Brain: Slash Command Execution Flow

    User->>Discord: /command [options]
    Discord->>JDA: SlashCommandInteractionEvent
    JDA->>Listener: onSlashCommandInteraction()

    Listener->>Manager: handleSlashCommand(event)
    Manager->>Manager: Lookup registered handler<br/>(by command name)

    alt Handler Found
        Manager->>Handler: handle(event)

        alt /settings (Components V2 Panel)
            Handler->>Handler: Create SettingsSession
            Handler->>CV2: Build Main View Container
            CV2->>Discord: reply(Container).ephemeral()
            Discord->>User: Show Settings Panel

            Note over User,CV2: User navigates via buttons
            User->>Discord: Click button (e.g. "🧩 Plugins")
            Discord->>Listener: ButtonInteractionEvent
            Listener->>Manager: route to @ButtonHandler("settings:")
            Manager->>CV2: Build Plugins View
            CV2->>Discord: editMessage(Container)
            Discord->>User: Show Plugins View

            Note over User,CV2: User toggles plugin
            User->>Discord: Click toggle button
            Discord->>Listener: ButtonInteractionEvent
            Listener->>Manager: handlePluginToggle()
            Manager->>Manager: guildSettingsService.disablePluginForGuild()
            Manager->>Manager: syncGuildCommands(guildId)
            Manager->>Discord: guild.updateCommands().submit()
            Discord->>User: Plugin slash commands disappear

        else Plugin Command
            alt Simple Response
                Handler->>Discord: event.reply("Response")
                Discord->>User: Show response
            else AI-Powered Response
                Handler->>Brain: process(message)
                Brain-->>Handler: Generated response
                Handler->>Discord: event.reply(response)
                Discord->>User: Show AI response
            end
        end
    else Handler Not Found
        Manager->>Discord: event.reply("Unknown command").ephemeral()
        Discord->>User: Show error (ephemeral)
    end

    Note over User,Brain: Command Registration Strategy

    rect rgb(40, 60, 40)
        Note right of Manager: Core commands: registered GLOBALLY<br/>(/settings)<br/><br/>Plugin commands: registered PER-GUILD<br/>Filtered by guild_settings.disabled_plugins<br/><br/>syncCommands() separates core vs plugin<br/>syncGuildCommands(id) updates one guild
    end
